channel.title: Online help
channel.description: Hi guys, I need help putting my server online. I have tried pretty much every tutorial and pretty much what i am confused with is where to change my ip's, what ip to change it to, and what client to zip, and what the ip in the zip client needs to be. I have teamviewer, i have skype, just let me know if anyone can help!

item.title: Online help
item.dc:creator: @noty noty
item.description:
@noty wrote:

[quote=“ikwooninjehuis, post:2, topic:428230”]1) Get no-ip
2) Make an no-ip account and make a ip (like slayerpkzz.no-ip.biz)
3) Log into the no-ip duc then put your link online

Now server sided:

  1. Go to client.java or server.java idk what ur using atm
  2. Search for 0.0.0.0 if it doesent works search for 127.0.0.1
  3. Change it to your link (ip)
  4. Compile and your done

Thats no-ip way if you want the hamachi way to ask me…[/quote]
u forgot portforwarding 192.168.0.1 for LinkSyS or just search on google for “how to portforward your router” and u go to that site and they will guide u till it
